@baseUrl = http://localhost:5206
@validAppointmentId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@defaultPatientId = 11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111
@secondPatientId = 22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222
@defaultDoctorId = bbbbbbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbbbbbbbbbb
@nonExistentId = 99999999-9999-9999-9999-999999999999

### ========== GET APPOINTMENT BY ID ==========

### 1. Get Appointment by ID (happy path - expect 200)
# First, book an appointment using the BookAppointment request, then use the returned ID here
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{validAppointmentId}}

### 2. Get Appointment by ID - Non-existent ID (expect 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{nonExistentId}}

### 3. Get Appointment by ID - Empty GUID (expect 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### ========== GET APPOINTMENTS (GENERAL QUERY) ==========

### 4. Get All Appointments - No filters (expect 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments

### 5. Get All Appointments - With pagination (page 1, size 10)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments?pageNumber=1&pageSize=10

### 6. Get Appointments - Filter by patient only (expect 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments?patientId={{defaultPatientId}}

### 7. Get Appointments - Filter by doctor only (expect 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments?doctorId={{defaultDoctorId}}

### 8. Get Appointments - Filter by status only (expect 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments?status=1

### 9. Get Appointments - Filter by date range only (expect 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments?startDate=2026-01-01&endDate=2026-12-31

### 10. Get Appointments - Filter by patient + doctor (expect 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments?patientId={{defaultPatientId}}&doctorId={{defaultDoctorId}}

### 11. Get Appointments - Filter by patient + status (expect 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments?patientId={{defaultPatientId}}&status=1

### 12. Get Appointments - All filters combined (expect 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments?patientId={{defaultPatientId}}&doctorId={{defaultDoctorId}}&status=1&startDate=2025-01-01&endDate=2025-12-31&pageNumber=1&pageSize=5

### 13. Get Appointments - Invalid page number (expect 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments?pageNumber=0

### 14. Get Appointments - Invalid page size (expect 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments?pageSize=150

### Note: Replace the validAppointmentId variable above with an actual appointment ID
### You can get one by:
### 1. Running the BookAppointment.http request
### 2. Copying the "id" from the response
### 3. Pasting it in the @validAppointmentId variable at the top of this file
